<section class="section experience-section" id="experience">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <p class="section-eyebrow">Career History</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">A track record across three countries and two decades.</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">
      Executive support in high-pressure, multinational environments. The kind of experience you don't get from courses.
    </p>

    <div class="timeline">

      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
        <div class="timeline-meta">
          <span class="timeline-period">Sep 2016 – Present</span>
          <span class="timeline-company">RMH Teleservice Asia-Pacific Inc. (Alorica)</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="timeline-role">IT Service Desk Quality Analyst</h3>
        <p class="timeline-location">Davao City, Philippines</p>
        <ul class="achievement-list">
          <li>Evaluated <strong>100+ calls, chats, and tickets monthly</strong> to assess performance — coaching that directly improved KPI outcomes across the team.</li>
          <li>Designed and implemented a <strong>QA-led attendance tracking system</strong> giving leadership real-time workforce visibility — a system built from scratch, still in use.</li>
          <li>Covered <strong>interim Lead on Duty responsibilities</strong>, running QA talks, maintaining floor operations, and fielding analyst escalations without disruption.</li>
          <li>Collaborated with leadership to <strong>rebuild process documentation</strong>, eliminating ambiguity and improving consistency across the entire QA team.</li>
          <li>Produced <strong>daily and weekly operational reports</strong> on AHT, adherence, and utilization to drive data-informed management decisions.</li>
          <li>Mentored and onboarded new hires across multiple roles, <strong>shortening ramp-up time</strong> and easing training transitions for incoming staff.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
        <div class="timeline-meta">
          <span class="timeline-period">Apr 2011 – Dec 2015</span>
          <span class="timeline-company">Bilfal Heavy Industries Ltd.</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="timeline-role">HR Supervisor</h3>
        <p class="timeline-location">Saudi Arabia</p>
        <ul class="achievement-list">
          <li>Managed day-to-day HR operations across security, transport, accommodation, and subcontractor functions — keeping a <strong>complex, multi-department organization</strong> running without disruption.</li>
          <li>Built and executed <strong>international recruitment strategies</strong> that hit 99% coordination efficiency and filled critical roles on schedule.</li>
          <li>Owned the <strong>full hiring cycle</strong> — JDs, screening, interviews, pre-employment assessments — across multiple concurrent roles simultaneously.</li>
          <li>Processed <strong>employment contracts and visa documentation end-to-end</strong>, ensuring zero deployment delays for incoming international personnel.</li>
          <li>Negotiated and maintained contracts with agencies, vendors, and subcontractors — <strong>saved 10%+ on recruitment fees</strong> through direct sourcing.</li>
          <li>Achieved <strong>100% documentation compliance across ISO and internal audits</strong>, with zero findings requiring corrective action.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-dot secondary"></div>
        <div class="timeline-meta">
          <span class="timeline-period">Apr 2008 – Oct 2009</span>
          <span class="timeline-company">Hassan Misfer Al Zahrani & Partners Co.</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="timeline-role">Executive Secretary</h3>
        <p class="timeline-location">Saudi Arabia</p>
        <ul class="achievement-list">
          <li>Managed <strong>executive calendars, travel itineraries, and communications</strong> for the CEO and senior leadership — including urgent cross-border coordination.</li>
          <li>Coordinated <strong>end-to-end recruitment for non-Arabic roles</strong>: sourcing, screenings, interviews across multiple departments.</li>
          <li>Processed visa applications and maintained complete documentation — achieving a <strong>99% successful deployment rate</strong> for executives and incoming employees.</li>
          <li>Reduced travel costs by <strong>directly booking arrangements for CEO and Board Directors</strong>, including visa applications and itinerary management.</li>
          <li>Negotiated directly with candidates and staffing agencies on terms and timelines — keeping <strong>hiring pipelines moving</strong> without bottlenecks.</li>
